        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Heart-hand syndrome refers to a group of congenital disorders characterized by malformations of the upper limbs and heart. To date heart-hand syndrome comprises the following rare syndromes; Holt-Oram syndrome; heart-hand syndrome type 2; heart-hand syndrome type 3; heart hand syndrome Slovenian type brachydactyly-long thumb; and patent ductus arteriosus-bicuspid aortic valve - hand anomalies."
        },
